title: ICE: `resolution failed during building vtable representation` `trait_alias`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(trait_alias)] trait Alias = A where i32: B; trait A {} trait B { fn test(&self); } trait C: Alias {} impl A for () {} impl C for () {} impl B for i32 { fn test(&self) {} } fn main() { let x: &C = &(); } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.70.0-nightly (1db9c061d 2023-03-21) binary: rustc commit-hash: 1db9c061d387a66ab16a90ec5a1b90adf216e2da commit-date: 2023-03-21 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.70.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.7 ``` ### Error output ``` ```
